<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sacrum\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sacrum<\/a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coccyx\" rel=\"nofollow\">Coccyx<\/a> are the last parts of the vertebral column. A tail is therefore, just an extension of the vertebral column. <\/p>\n\n<h1>How does it look like in humans?<\/h1>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/4N1APm.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/4N1APm.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/3gGSx.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/3gGSx.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<h1>Is it really a tail that we see?<\/h1>\n\n<p>Yes! Human embryo have been dissected and histologic analyses were performed. There are no doubt, it is a tail!<\/p>\n\n<p>See <a href=\"http://www.humanpathol.com/article/S0046-8177(84)80079-9/abstract\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dao and Netski (1984)<\/a>, <a href=\"http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002234689190343R\" rel=\"nofollow\">Belzberg et al. (1991)<\/a> and <a href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/aja.1001520108/abstract\" rel=\"nofollow\">Fallon and Simandi (2005)<\/a> for further description and evidence.<\/p>\n\n<h1>FUN FACT<\/h1>\n\n<p>In some rare cases, humans can get born with a tail. These tails can then be removed by surgical procedure. Such procedure are quite simple and are not really recent (<a href=\"http://thejns.org/doi/abs/10.3171/jns.1985.63.3.0461?journalCode=jns\" rel=\"nofollow\">Speigelmann et al. 1985<\/a>).<\/p>\n","answer_id":44673,"question_id":44661,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1459211367}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/44661/how-scientists-can-be-confident-that-human-embryo-tail-is-really-a-tail","last_activity_date":1459211367,"creation_date":1459147783,"answer_count":3,"title":"How scientists can be confident that human embryo tail is really a tail?","body":"<p>From <a href