 energy, like when you want fire, you need oxygen."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/56b4833d86d3cccc3ccfd6eeaf0b767e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14946,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14946/mdperry","reputation":2645,"display_name":"mdperry"},"score":0,"post_id":40055,"edited":false,"creation_date":1446202279,"comment_id":67325,"body":"As wonderful and abundant oxygen is, it is also highly reactive (consider rusted metal), and can contain ozone and oxygen singlets (a free radical). Free radicals are highly mutagenic and lead to double-stranded breaks in DNA. When cells die by programmed cell death they lyse their mitochondria, possibly to hasten the process. Finally, the enzyme super oxide dismutase exists to safely remove these free radicals from cells."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":11,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5ea8dd43bed181174b9fccfed2ea2c88?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":9249,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9249/plasmahh","reputation":101,"display_name":"PlasmaHH"},"score":5,"post_id":40056,"edited":false,"creation_date":1446135246,"comment_id":67249,"body":"&quot;Because it is so abundant in the atmosphere, it doesn&#39;t make sense to store it.&quot; this makes only sense today, it made no sense when the first photosynthesis was done."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/PObJM.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4264,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4264/jan-dvorak","reputation":101,"display_name":"Jan Dvorak"},"score":0,"post_id":40056,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5