r with our hands.<\/p>\n\n<p>(yes my hand show the same slight bend in the fingers)<\/p>\n","answer_id":44619,"question_id":44608,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/jlp4Q.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5198,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5198/anongoodnurse","reputation":12148,"display_name":"anongoodnurse"},"score":0,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":1,"post_id":44622,"edited":false,"creation_date":1458998851,"comment_id":77839,"body":"Is it always the case? Do all people have this kind of hand structure? Are there any studies that say so?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/jlp4Q.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5198,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5198/anongoodnurse","reputation":12148,"display_name":"anongoodnurse"},"score":0,"post_id":44622,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"edited":false,"creation_date":1459002086,"comment_id":77841,"body":"@WYSIWYG - This is, as I said, &quot;normal&quot;. I&#39;m sure it&#39;s in an anatomy textbook someplace. Does it sound wrong to you?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":1,"post_id":44622,"edited":false,"creation_date":1459003008,"comment_id":77842,"body":"No. The theory sounds quite plausible but I haven&#39;t come across any text that actually pinpoints 