ble to grasp and manipulate objects of a wide variety of shapes.<\/p>\n\n<p>It also allows fine manipulation of thumb and fingers. Touching each fingertip to the tip of the thumb quickly shows the same effect - the fingertips approximately align with the thumb. If they didn't align this way, we would lose some of our very fine (as in requiring great precision, not as in quality) motor skills.<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm not going to hypothesize on why the hand evolved the way it did; it's very efficient and that seems reason enough.<\/p>\n","answer_id":44622,"question_id":44608,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1458957282}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/44608/the-alignment-of-fingers-in-our-hand","last_activity_date":1458958505,"creation_date":1458898297,"answer_count":2,"title":"The alignment of fingers in our hand","body":"<p>I noticed that in my hand the index and middle finger are aligned in one direction and the next two fingers somewhat in the opposite direction. My question is, why are our fingers aligned in that way?\nMoreover, is it of any evolutionary significance?<\/p>\n\n<p>For clarity, I am posting a picture of my hand.<a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/kG1kg.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/kG1kg.jpg\" alt=\"hand\"><\/a><\/p>\n","question_id":44608,"tags":["human-anatomy","morphology"],"score":1,"accepted_answer_id":44622,"down_vote_count":1,"is_answered":true,"view_count":67,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1458958505},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Kyg92.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6061,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6061/rhill45","reputation":2493,"display_name":"rhill45","accept_rate":79},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":3