>\n<li>But <strong>perhaps<\/strong> when I think of sea turtles and pat my stomach at the same time, I produce the same set of waves as <code>A2<\/code> (opening and closing my left hand)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>My question is: is this a concern/possibility with EEG/ERP? In other words, can multiple overt/covert intents produce identical wave activity (hence, identical EEG readings)?<\/p>\n","question_id":44388,"tags":["neuroscience","electroencephalography"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":44395,"down_vote_count":2,"is_answered":true,"view_count":91,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/WZOSZ.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":22337,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22337/devnull","reputation":118,"display_name":"DevNull"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d1c6641d5c8556d9f351765c89b510f6?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":19493,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19493/david-blomstrom","reputation":1247,"display_name":"David Blomstrom"},"score":3,"post_id":43965,"edited":false,"creation_date":1457151251,"comment_id":76310,"body":"Interesting question. I wonder if the answer might possibly be similar to the avocado story -- <a href=\"http://theplate.nationalgeographic.com/2015/01/05/avocado-guacamole/\" rel=\"nofollow\">theplate.nationalgeographic.com/2015/01/05/avocado-guacamole<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1e757e9168975c1ba26ba627de65ab8e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":20449,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/20449/polisetty","reputation":352,"display_name":"Polisetty","accept_rate":25},"score":1,"post_id":43965,"edited":false,"creation_date":1457158336,"comment_id":76313,"body":"I don&#39;t remember much, had studied botany a long time ago. But isn&#39;t cucurbitaceae that genus where the fruit blasts to disperse the seeds?? Then you dont need animals to 