ates with body size. What you may ask here is: Can our brain size to body size ratio increase? Probably yes... I can't think of a reason, why not?<\/p>\n\n<p>But please please be aware of that intelligence, does not have to correlate with brain size. e.g. elephants and humans. There may be some limits of the smallest possible brain size for certain mental tasks and skills. But wiring and plasticity is probably more important than the bulk size.<\/p>\n","answer_id":44607,"question_id":44606,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/44606/the-evolution-of-the-human-brain-size","last_activity_date":1458892950,"creation_date":1458888580,"answer_count":1,"title":"the evolution of the human brain size","body":"<p>I was thinking, as I know, sometimes the process of producing <code>DNA<\/code> did not work well(<strong>correct me if I'm wrong<\/strong>), so it gives us some changes in the <em>object<\/em> we gonna have(for example: increasing or decreasing a part, enabling  or disabling  a part), <em>could human brain grow more that it is now<\/em>?<\/p>\n","question_id":44606,"tags":["human-biology","evolution","brain"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":44607,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"primarily opinion-based","is_answered":true,"view_count":33,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31bd000e05d1906761be4d001a440dd7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":13493,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13493/jagmeet-singh","reputation":51,"display_name":"Jagmeet Singh"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/04e6ee2e426f6de74b6d5c4ec3833bc2?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":22357,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22357/maljam","reputation":387,"display_name":"Maljam"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31bd000e05d1906761be4d001a440dd7?s=128