o the heart. The major muscles of the legs have large veins that will fill during the relaxation stage of the movement, and the muscle contraction in the active movement pushes the blood back into the circulatory system. Increasing blood flow triggers a faster heartbeat. Because the heart muscle of conditioned athletes enlarges and strengthens, the hearts of athletes pump more blood per beat. <a href=\"http://www.livestrong.com/article/385209-why-do-athletes-have-a-lower-heart-rate/\" rel=\"nofollow\">1<\/a><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","answer_id":43413,"question_id":43352,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1455877629}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/43352/is-an-athletes-heart-rate-after-exercise-greater-than-a-non-athlete","last_activity_date":1458831702,"creation_date":1455542302,"answer_count":1,"title":"Is an athlete's heart rate after exercise greater than a non-athlete","body":"<p>I was just wondering \nAnd if it is greater or lower how does this benefit an athlete \nAlso what is the averaged number of heart beats per minute<\/p>\n","question_id":43352,"tags":["human-biology","breathing","heart-output"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":43413,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"unclear what you're asking","is_answered":true,"view_count":117,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1458831702},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bee37ff3471620d9a17e619e022b547d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1061,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1061/emanuele","reputation":270,"display_name":"emanuele"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":1,"post_id":34931,"edited":false,"creation_date":1433462206,"comment_id":56406,"body":"What do you mean with &quot;over fit&quot;?"},{"owner":{"pro